.TH LABYRINTH 1 "April 2026" "Labyrinth 0.3.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
labyrinth \- pure Go recursive DNS resolver
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B labyrinth
[\fIflags\fR] [\fIcommand\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Labyrinth
is a recursive-only DNS resolver written in pure Go with zero external
dependencies. It receives DNS queries from clients, navigates the global DNS
hierarchy from root servers down to authoritative nameservers, caches results,
and returns answers \(em all within a single, statically compiled binary.
.PP
Labyrinth does not serve authoritative zones. It does one thing \(em recursive
resolution \(em and does it correctly, safely, and fast.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B check
Validate the configuration file and exit.
.TP
.B version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.B hash " " \fIpassword\fR
Generate bcrypt password hash for config file.
.TP
.B daemon " " start|stop|status
Manage background daemon process.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-listen " " \fIaddress\fR
Listen address for DNS queries (default ":53").
.TP
.BR \-metrics " " \fIaddress\fR
Metrics HTTP endpoint address (default "127.0.0.1:9153").
.TP
.BR \-config " " \fIpath\fR
Configuration file path (default "labyrinth.yaml").
.TP
.BR \-log\-level " " \fIlevel\fR
Log level: debug, info, warn, error (default "info").
.TP
.BR \-log\-format " " \fIformat\fR
Log format: json, text (default "json").
.TP
.BR \-cache\-size " " \fIn\fR
Maximum cache entries (default 100000).
.TP
.BR \-web " " \fIaddress\fR
Web dashboard address (overrides config).
.TP
.BR \-daemon
Run as background daemon.
.TP
.BR \-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is loaded in this priority order (highest first):
.IP 1. 4
CLI flags
.IP 2.
Environment variables (prefix: LABYRINTH_)
.IP 3.
Configuration file (labyrinth.yaml)
.IP 4.
Compiled defaults
.PP
See
.I labyrinth.yaml
for a complete list of configuration options.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B LABYRINTH_SERVER_LISTEN_ADDR
Override server listen address.
.TP
.B LABYRINTH_SERVER_METRICS_ADDR
Override metrics HTTP address.
.TP
.B LABYRINTH_LOGGING_LEVEL
Override log level.
.TP
.B LABYRINTH_LOGGING_FORMAT
Override log format.
.TP
.B LABYRINTH_CACHE_MAX_ENTRIES
Override maximum cache entries.
.TP
.B LABYRINTH_RESOLVER_MAX_DEPTH
Override maximum resolution depth.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGINT, SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown. Stops accepting new connections, waits for in-flight
queries to complete (grace period configurable), then exits.
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Flush entire cache.
.TP
.B SIGUSR2
Dump cache statistics to log.
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Log config reload notification.
.SH HTTP ENDPOINTS
.TP
.B GET /metrics
Prometheus-compatible metrics in text exposition format.
.TP
.B GET /health
JSON health check: {"status":"healthy","cache_entries":N,"uptime":"..."}
.TP
.B GET /ready
Readiness probe. Returns 200 after root hint priming is complete, 503 during startup.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start with defaults:
.PP
.RS
.B labyrinth
.RE
.PP
Start with custom listen address and debug logging:
.PP
.RS
.B labyrinth -listen 0.0.0.0:5353 -log-level debug -log-format text
.RE
.PP
Validate configuration:
.PP
.RS
.B labyrinth -config /etc/labyrinth/labyrinth.yaml check
.RE
.PP
Query the running resolver:
.PP
.RS
.B dig @localhost google.com A
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I labyrinth.yaml
Default configuration file (searched in current directory).
.TP
.I /etc/labyrinth/labyrinth.yaml
Recommended location for system-wide configuration.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dig (1),
.BR unbound (8),
.BR named (8)
